\pard\f0\fs28 A very variable plant, especially in the size and shape of the leaves. Some segregates, especially {\b S. micranthum} DC. in Lam. & DC.,{\i  Fl. Fr.} ed. 3, {\b 5}: 523 (1815) ({\i S. album} subsp. {\i micranthum} (DC.) Syme), from S.W. & S.C. Europe, with short stems, small flowers and rather short leaves, are sufficiently striking to have been given specific or subspecific rank, but intermediate plants are so numerous as to make their diagnosis impossible.
