\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. S. gypsicola} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i Diagn. Pl. Nov. Hisp.} 14 (1842). Like {\b 23} in habit, inflorescence and flowers, but with flatter, ovate-rhombic, greyish, densely puberulent leaves, closely imbricate in 5 rows on the sterile shoots. 2n = 68, 102. {\i C. & S. Spain}. Hs.
