\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 25. S. subulatum} (C.A. Meyer) Boiss.,{\i  Fl. Or.}{\b  2}: 783 (1872). Like larger variants of{\b  23} but erect flowering shoots glabrous throughout; often taller, with linear-subulate, acuminate leaves 10 × 1·5 mm; inflorescence more compact, with shorter pedicels; petals 5-6 mm; styles almost equalling the ovaries. 2n = 18. {\i  S.E. Russia.} Rs(E). ({\i S.W. Asia}.)
\par

