\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. S. anglicum} Hudson,{\i  Fl. Angl.} ed. 2,196 (1778). Glabrous, laxly caespitose perennial with creeping stems bearing short non-flowering shoots and flowering stems up to 15 cm, but usually much less. Leaves 3-5 mm, cylindrical, ovoid or subglobose, gibbous, spurred, alternate, often pink. Flowers 5-merous, usually rather crowded in a small cyme with 2 or 3 branches and leaf-like bracts. Sepals free, spurred. Petals 2·5-4·5 mm, acute to acuminate, pink or white. Stamens 10, with blackish anthers. Follicles red, stellate-patent. Seeds orange-brown to red. {\i Calcifuge. W. Europe, extending to S.W. Sweden}. Br Ga Hb Hs Lu No Su.
\par

