\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. S. stefco} Stefanov, {\i God. Sof. Univ.} ({\i Agro.-Les. Fak}.){\b  24}({\b 2}): 105 (1946). Small, glabrous perennial; flowering stems 7-10 cm. Leaves 4-5 × 1·5 mm, cylindrical, alternate, bright pink. Flowers 4-merous, shortly stalked, in a rather dense cyme. Petals 4-5 mm, acute, suberect, pale pink. Stamens 8. Follicles stellate-patent; styles very short. Seeds brown. 2n = 14.•  {\i  Mountains of S.W. Bulgaria and N. Greece.} Bu Gr.
\par

