\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. S. alsinifolium} All.,{\i  Fl. Pedem. }{\b 2}: 119 (1785). Delicate, glandular-pubescent annual; flowering stems 10-15 cm, weak and spreading. Leaves 10-15(-20) mm, alternate, oblong to elliptical, relatively thin, the lower petiolate. Flowers 5-merous, on long, slender pedicels, in a leafy, very lax panicle. Petals 5-6 mm, ovate-rhombic, acuminate, white. Stamens 10; filaments 3·5-5 mm. Follicles whitish, erect, pubescent. 2n = 26.{\i  Shady, schistose rocks and caves. • N.W. Italy.} It.
